    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nwhen search/replacing using `:s/../../gc` one can do `y`and `n` to replace and skip. if you mistakenly pressed either y or n there is no easy way to go back\n\n\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nIntroduce a `N` action that will go to the previous substitution and re-ask `y/n/a/ql/..`  \n\nThe to easiest support is probably if the user mistakenly pressed `n` then he can do a `N` for back, then `y` to replace.\n\nit would be cool if the reverse situation is also supported - that you accidentally replaced something and you can go back `N`, and undo the replace with `n` which then takes the user forward to the next replace spot",
